Students at Fun Dance Company proved their passion for dancing as they excelled in the annual Acrobatic Federation of South Africa (Afsa) exams recently.
The dance company obtained a 100% pass rate with 28 of the 31 students scoring 90% and above with honours and distinctions. The lowest marks recorded on the day are between 85% and 89% with honours. Two students, Rami Chuene and Ramatethje Mphahlele obtained the highest marks as they scored 98%.
Fun Dance Company owner Olivia Fox-Venter indicated that one of the students, Carina Froehlich qualified to be an acrobatic dance teacher. She stated that they were proud of the girls, adding that their hard work is showing in the exam results.
Story: ENDY SENYATSI
